      • loadGraph

        private Graph<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer> loadGraph(java.io.File file)
        Loads an undirected graph from a text file.

        Fileformat:

        • Each line represents a vertex, the content is the vertex name.
        • Lines consisting only of white spaces or empty ones are ignored.
        • Two consecutive lines build an edge.
        • A remaining single vertex is not allowed.
        Parameters:
        file - File to load.
        Returns:
        True if graph is loaded, false otherwise.

      • saveBicliques

        private void saveBicliques(java.io.File file,
                           java.util.Set<Biclique<java.lang.String,java.lang.Integer>> setOfMaxBicliques)
        Saves an set of bicliques in a text file.

        Fileformat:

        • Each line represents a vertex, the content is the vertex name.
        • After each partition of vertices an empty line is placed.
        Parameters:
        file - File to save.
        setOfMaxBicliques - Set of bicliques to save.
